===================
=  README for ex8 =
===================
car.py
board.py
game.py

==================
=  Description:  =
==================

A rush hour game:
`````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````
-car.py contains the Car class. We define all the attributes of a car,
and list_locations method, to check every place taken by a car.
It also contains Direction class

-board.py contains the Board class. This class representing the rush hour game.
It have the size of the board, the cars on it, and the exit location as
attributes. And many methods used to print a representation of the board,
or to move/add a car to the board

-game.py contains the Game class, that's handling the game,
responsible to the interaction with the user, checking that all legal
(regarding the rules) and checking victory